title: Two climbers dead after fall from El Capitan in Yosemite
content: Two climbers fell to their deaths early Saturday while climbing the Freeblast Route on El Capitan inside Yosemite National Park, authorities said.    Park Rangers and search and rescue teams responded to El Capitan after receiving multiple 911 calls at about 8:15 a.m. Saturday reporting the fall.    The identity of the climbers will not be released until family is notified, according to the National Park Service.    The investigation is ongoing and no further information will be released Saturday, authorities said.
